sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User as User / Git / MCP Client

    box External Triggers
        participant Triggers as Filesystem / Git / MCP events
    end

    box Runtime Coordination
        participant Monitor as Event Monitoring Layer
        participant Analysis as Incremental Analysis Layer
    end

    box Cognitive State
        participant Cache as Background Concept Cache
        participant Recall as Recall Engine
    end

    box Integration Boundaries
        participant AI as AI Provider Abstraction
        participant MCP as MCP Server
        participant Dispatch as Presentation Dispatch
    end

    box Delivery Surfaces
        participant Surfaces as Terminal / MCP experience
    end

    User->>Triggers: Produce change signals or requests
    Triggers->>Monitor: Normalize incoming events
    Monitor->>Analysis: Forward relevant work incrementally
    Analysis->>Cache: Update concept state
    Analysis->>Recall: Request recall opportunities
    Cache->>Recall: Supply retained context
    Recall->>AI: Synthesize or enrich prompts when needed
    AI-->>Recall: Return model output
    Recall->>Dispatch: Hand off user-facing result
    Dispatch->>Surfaces: Route to terminal or MCP channel
    MCP->>Monitor: Submit tool-driven requests into the same flow
    Dispatch->>MCP: Deliver MCP-facing responses
    Surfaces-->>User: Present recall prompt or feedback
